com.davidjarski.vfatreader

Class DirectoryEntry

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.davidjarski.vfatreader.DirectoryEntry

  • public class DirectoryEntry
extends java.lang.Object
    A DirectoryEntry is a data structure representing a single directory entry.
    Author:
    David Jarski (c) 2014-07-31

      • createEntry

        public static DirectoryEntry createEntry(java.lang.String filename,
                         byte[] buffer,
                         int offset)
                                  throws java.io.IOException
        Factory method for creating a DirectoryEntry.
        Parameters:
        filename - the long filename - null references are not accepted - use an empty String instead.
        buffer - an array containing the short entry of the directory entry
        offset - points to the first byte of the short entry
        Returns:
        a new instance of DirectoryEntry
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - if an error is encountered while parsing the entry

      • isDeleted

        public static boolean isDeleted(byte[] buffer,

        Returns true if the directory entry at buffer[offset] is marked as deleted.

        No attempt is made to verify that buffer[offset] actually points to the first byte of a directory entry.
        Parameters:
        buffer - an array containing the the directory entry
        offset - points to the first byte of the entry
        Returns:
        true if the entry is marked deleted, false otherwise

      • getAttributes

        public byte getAttributes()
        Returns the bit-packed attribute of this entry.
        The bits are packed as follows:
         READ_ONLY_MASK  0x01
 HIDDEN_MASK     0x02
 SYSTEM_MASK     0x04
 VOLUME_MASK     0x08
 DIRECTORY_MASK  0x10
 ARCHIVE_MASK    0x20
        Returns:
        the bit-packed attributes of this entry

      • getCreationTime

        public short getCreationTime()
        Returns the bit-packed creation time of this entry.
        The bits are packed as follows:
         [0-4]   seconds (in 2-second intervals)
 [5-10]  minutes (0-60)
 [11-15] hour of the day (0-24)
        Returns:
        the creation time

      • getCreationDate

        public short getCreationDate()
        Returns the bit-packed creation date of this entry.
        The bits are packed as follows:
         [0-4]  day of month (1-31)
 [5-8]  month of year (1-12)
 [9-15] years since 1980 (0-127)
        Returns:
        the creation date

      • getLastAccessDate

 [5-8]  month of year (1-12)
 [9-15] years since 1980 (0-127)
        Returns:
        the last access date

      • getLastWriteTime
